comments: Theis (BOS) briefly locks arms with Lopez (WAS) and the two players disengage off ball.
Tatum's (BOS) off-arm brushes across Beal's (WAS) back at the end of the drive. The contact is marginal and does not affect Beal's ability to defend.
Lopez (WAS) gathers the ball and legally takes two steps before his shot attempt.
Tatum (BOS) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Neto's (WAS) path and does not deliver any contact.
Lopez (WAS) maintains a legal guarding position as he defends Walker's (BOS) driving shot attempt.
Walker (BOS) places his non-shooting arm away from his body but does not extend or deliver any contact to Lopez (WAS) during the shot attempt.
Neto (WAS) makes marginal contact with Theis (BOS) as he taps the rebound away from Theis.
Green (BOS) is in the lane for longer than three seconds without actively guarding an opponent.
Green (BOS) jumps vertically and absorbs the lower body contact as Beal (WAS) finishes his driving shot attempt on the opposite side of the basket.
Walker (BOS) establishes himself in a legal screening position in  Lopez's (WAS) path.
Theis (BOS) establishes himself in a legal picking position in Beal's (WAS) path.
Theis (BOS) legally contests Westbrook's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Bonga (WAS) jumps vertically and absorbs the marginal contact created by Tatum's (BOS) leg during his driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (WAS) engages then disengages with Ojeleye (BOS) during the screen.
Replay review of the play confirms the out of bounds call. Beal (WAS) naturally loses his footing and steps out of bounds. Possession is correctly awarded to BOS.
As Hachimura (WAS) jumps vertically to defend the shot attempt, Tatum (BOS) places his non-shooting arm away from his body and briefly makes contact with Hachimura's front.
Beal (WAS) absorbs the contact as Tatum (BOS) jumps backwards into Beal during the driving shot attempt.
Green (BOS) and Bertans (WAS) make incidental contact with each other as the two players meet running in different directions on the floor.
Tatum (BOS) makes marginal contact with Beal's (WAS) arm after the release that does not affect his jump shot attempt.
